  "prompt": "Why was I blocked from adding questions on quora anonymously and how can I change it?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you were blocked from adding questions on Quora anonymously. Here are some common reasons:\n\n1. **Violation of Quora's Policies:** If you violated Quora's guidelines or policies, such as posting inappropriate, spammy, or offensive content, your ability to post questions anonymously might be restricted.\n\n2. **Suspicious Activity:** If Quora detected suspicious activity from your account, such as repeatedly posting similar questions or engaging in behavior that appears automated, they might block your anonymous posting privileges.\n\n3. **User Reports:** If other users have reported your anonymous questions for being inappropriate or violating guidelines, Quora may take action by restricting your anonymous posting.\n\n4. **Technical Issues:** Occasionally, technical glitches or bugs could cause temporary restrictions on certain features, including anonymous posting.\n\nTo address the issue and potentially regain the ability to post questions anonymously, you can take the following steps:\n\n1. **Review Quora's Policies:** Ensure that you understand and adhere to Quora's guidelines and policies. Avoid posting content that might be considered inappropriate or spammy.\n\n2. **Contact Quora Support:** Reach out to Quora's support team to inquire about the specific reason for the restriction and ask for guidance on how to resolve the issue. You can do this by visiting the Quora Help Center and submitting a request or finding relevant contact options.\n\n3. **Improve Your Account Standing:** If the restriction is due to your account's behavior or reports from other users, focus on improving your account's standing by posting quality content and engaging positively with the community.\n\n4. **Wait and Monitor:** If the restriction is temporary or due to a technical issue, it might resolve on its own. Keep an eye on your account and see if the ability to post anonymously is restored after some time.\n\nRemember to always follow community guidelines and engage respectfully to avoid future issues.",
